### 🚨 COST DOCTRINE — INTERNALIZE BEFORE ANY READ OP

X PPU bills **per-user-returned**, not per-call, on user-list endpoints (`/following`, `/followers`, etc). One `?max_results=100` call returning 100 user objects = **$1.00**, not $0.01. The graph walk burned $70 in 30 minutes.

**Cheap surfaces (~$0.001-0.005 each):** owned bookmarks, owned tweets, search/recent, single-tweet GET, write ops (follow/unfollow ~$0.01 each).

**Expensive surfaces (per-user-billed):** /following, /followers, /retweeted_by, /liked_by, /lists/:id/members, any endpoint returning user object lists. **NEVER paginate these without an explicit cost-line approval.**

**Stream cost is generally fine** — only delivered tweets count (~$0.005 each). 89 tweets captured before kill = ~$0.45.

