## FOREVER-RULE

> Before any "how do I X" architecture question, before any axiom proposal, before any "state of art on Y" claim: run `research triangulate "<query>"`. Single-source claims are phantom-substrate of doctrine — they pass surface inspection ("I read it somewhere") but fail substrate probe ("which source, fetched when, what's the consensus?"). Cite source-id + fetch-ts in every proposal that depends on external claims. Pattern P22 strike-1.

---

